    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures.wait and as_completed function identity — wait.__name__=='wait'(len=4); wait.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; wait.__qualname__=='wait'; as_completed.__name__=='as_completed'(len=12); as_completed.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; as_completed.__qualname__=='as_completed'; FIRST_COMPLETED.__class__.__name__=='str'; ALL_COMPLETED.__class__.__name__=='str'."
    - "concurrent.futures.wait and concurrent.futures.as_completed are both module-level functions defined in concurrent.futures._base and re-exported from concurrent.futures. Both __module__ values are 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "concurrent.futures.FIRST_COMPLETED and ALL_COMPLETED are string constants ('FIRST_COMPLETED' and 'ALL_COMPLETED' respectively). Their __class__.__name__ is 'str'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Table 1: concurrent.futures.wait function identity — __name__, __module__, __qualname__
#
# concurrent.futures.wait.__name__ == 'wait' (len=4)
# concurrent.futures.wait.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'
# concurrent.futures.wait.__qualname__ == 'wait'
#
# concurrent.futures.wait blocks until the given futures complete.
# It is defined in concurrent.futures._base and re-exported from the package.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra180.wait_func_identity:
  description: "concurrent.futures.wait function identity: __name__=='wait'(len=4), __module__=='concurrent.futures._base', __qualname__=='wait'; new to concurrent_futures_extra180"
